<TEXT>
charlotte porter news editor for the associated 
press bureau in atlanta has been named assistant chief of bureau 
the appointment was announced thursday by chief of bureau carl 
bell 
ms porter 34 joined the ap in minneapolis in 1976 she worked 
in the sioux falls and pierre sd bureaus before transferring to 
the general desk at aps new york headquarters in 1979 the atlanta 
news editorship followed in 1988 
ms porter grew up in lenoir nc and is a graduate of 
macalester college in st paul minn 
in atlanta she succeeds matt bokor who has resigned to join the 
miami herald 
</TEXT>
