<TEXT>
a sunny mild winter with no rain has 
inspired italian designers to rethink their coldweather wardrobes 
for the fallwinter ready to wear collections which ended here 
thursday there are practically none of the usual rainccats heavy 
shearlings and sumptuous furs that usually mark the coming of winter 
italian style 
instead designers played heavily on lighter wool coats capes 
shawls and every possible shape of jacket from the blazer to the 
blouson 
fake furs and fur lookalike fabrics served the double purpose 
of placating conservationists and offering cheaper cooler 
alternatives to the traditional wraps 
the biggest champion for the ecological cause was milans 
numero uno giorgio armani who showed stoles jackets and even 
floor length coats in synthetic substitutes of leopard tiger 
panther among others as the fake furs were paraded down the runway 
a voice speaking for the animal world announced thank you armani 
for saving our skins 
fendi famous for their extravagant furs also nodded in the 
