<TEXT>
the good news from the milan winter runway 
which kicks off a new fashion decade is that women can wear what 
they like and still be in style 
no single trend or style emerged in this weeks showings of the 
italian readytowear collections for the fallwinter 198990 
rather it was a mixed fashion bag full of goodlooking clothes 
which dont require a perfect body 
hemlines range from the thigh to the floor skirts come in tight 
and loose versions jackets tend to be short but can also be 
threequarter there are trousers for every taste and configuration 
solid colors abound but so do plaid floral and paisley prints 
in general the designers stay away from the sexy aggressiveness 
epitomized by the miniskirt the italian rage several seasons ago 
to present a quieter more casual style dropped shoulders long 
languid lines and completely flat footwear 
the color scheme draws inspiration from the shades of an autumn 
forest brown moss green burnt yellow and berry blues and reds 
orange and fuchsia are the favorite shocking shades gray and black 
show up in every collection 
as always with italian readytowear these outfits are based on 
the good tailoring and beautiful fabrics which have become the 
trademark of the moda milanese milan fashion 
some say the designers put their pocket books before their 
creative talents in this latest round of collections 
but according to marjorie deane a us consultant who puts out 
her own fashion report this is not necessarily a sin 
luxury italian readytowear is our bestseller she said 
there might not be big news here but it will be a very popular 
season women will feel good in these clothes and why shouldnt 
they 
the hottest item on the milan winter runway is the coat as big 
and cozy as possible with broad shawl collar and ample dropped 
sleeve and a hemline which often grazes the floor some coats have 
hoods others are worn with long wool or fur scarves 
capes and threequarter jackets also play heavily in the 
collections 
for the animallover the designers offer fake furs made out of 
wooly synthetic fabrics to look like everything from sable to 
leopard fabric printed with animal spots and stripes is another 
ecologically minded option 
some of the winter offerings of italys top readytowear 
designers 
armani the curved hem tulipshaped skirt floral printed silk 
quilted jackets and a whole zoo of fun fake furs 
