thenwhite house chief of staff james a baker iii took the position 
at the june 25 1984 meeting of the national security planning group 
that it was illegal to solicit thirdcountry aid 
i took it to mean that if the president were to authorize 
money from third countries that would be a violation of law and 
he could therefore be so charged and impeached removed from 
office said mcfarlane members of the planning group included the 
president vice president and secretaries of state and defense 
mcfarlane recalled that bakers view was strongly countered 
and that the consensus from the meeting was that bakers opinion was 
not true 
saudi arabia that year began giving the contras 1 million a 
month 
