food inc which stands for farmers of ongoing determination 
produced a calendar called dakota men which pictured a young 
man for each month the 1988 calendar featured north dakota farmers 
the 89 issue contains farmers from both dakotas 
the venture was launched in 1987 but ran into serious trouble 
last year when an audit revealed that some of the 175508 raised 
from the sale of the first calendars in 1988 had been spent on 
questionable expenses including parties and none went to charities 
