television which promises wallsized tv screens with the clarity 
of 35 mm film use a world production standard of 1250 
sequentially scanned lines and 50 frames per second the united 
states in 1984 proposed a 1125 line60 frame standard and since 
that time has received the backing of japan canada and mexico 
the stakes are high for the united states which fears that 
multiple standards would jeopardize overseas sales of us movies 
and tv programs 
