one of three young men charged with killing 
a convenience store clerk while they were teenagers killed himself 
friday four hours before a jury was to resume deliberating his 
guilt or innocence 
scott davis 21 on trial at guntersville on a capital murder 
charge in the 1985 killing of missy macon shot himself at his 
familys home in ragland without leaving a suicide note coroner 
charles forman said he had been free on bond since shortly after 
the killing 
his two codefendants are serving life prison terms 
davis had claimed the three honor students were playing a fantasy 
game when mrs macon was shot 
davis attorney louis wilkinson told the jury at guntersville 
where the trial was moved because of publicity in st clair county 
that davis thought his companions cayce moore and chris white were 
going to pretend to rob the store where mrs macon worked 
davis had said he did not realize it was not a game until he 
heard the shot that killed mrs macon and saw moore leave the store 
with a bottle of wine 
when i saw the wine i knew right then that something bad had 
happened because when youre 17 you cant buy wine davis said 
he really honest to god thought it was going to be something 
harmless wilkinson said 
moore was convicted in september 1987 of capital murder and 
sentenced to life without parole white later pleaded guilty to 
murder and also received a life sentence with the possibility of 
parole 
davis and moore were 17 at the time of the killing while white 
was 14 
white has testified there was no discussion of playing any 
fantasy game before he and the two other went to the store 
earlier this week davis had testified that the night of mrs 
macons killing moore asked him if he had a death wish davis said 
that in the game top secret that meant a character had gone as 
far as he could and would go against something he could not beat 
davis said he told moore he did have a death wish 
i guess i meant i wanted to play he said 
on thursday the prosecution introduced two suicide notes written 
by davis to his parents the day after mrs macons death 
mom i wish a million times that i hadnt done it davis read 
from one of the notes 
we all thought it was a dream but that dream turned into a 
nightmare killing the lady didnt bother me but being without you 
is like a living hell 
mom i knew it was wrong for us to do it it started out as a 
game 
district attorney van davis said davis knew of the plan to rob 
the store and helped plan it 
this game stuff was fabricated for one reason defense of 
murder the prosecutor said the real issue is missy macon lying 
on the floor of that convenience store in a pool of blood and that 
cash register cleaned out 
there is no reason on earth why missy macon has to be dead 
nowhere is it written that defense for a murder is that you were 
playing a game 
the prosecutor said he thought they robbed a store in ragland 
rather than somewhere they were not known because they were so 
taken in by how smart they were and by how good they were at these 
games they thought they could rob and kill anywhere and get away 
with it 
after the shooting the three drove to florida where davis said 
he and moore planned to kill themselves 
we decided we couldnt live anymore davis said they later 
decided against committing suicide and were arrested at a rest stop 
