<TEXT>
a southern illinois university student 
placed racist jokes in the universitys computer system using 
another students access code and the list later turned up in a 
kindergarten class school officials said friday 
although the university per se did not have any direct 
involvement the individuals represent the university and we simply 
cannot condone this matter siu president john guyon said 
he did not identify the students involved but said the university 
was considering disciplinary action the jokes were directed 
primarily at blacks 
the president of the local naacp chapter nathaniel felder who 
also is director of planning and computing for the university 
system said he was pleased that siu took the matter seriously 
blacks make up about 10 percent of the 24227member student body at 
siucarbondale 
other than that felder said i cant comment on the 
university report 
siu learned of the problem in december when a 5yearold black 
boy took home used university computer printouts that had been given 
to his kindergarten class for use as scratch paper 
one month later the same child took home another siu printout 
that was part of the same joke list his mother then contacted the 
naacp which urged the university to investigate 
guyon appointed a committee jan 16 to investigate and its 
report released friday concluded that an undergraduate student put 
the joke file about 30 pages long into the universitys computer 
system sometime last fall 
the file was printed in november in the campus central computer 
facility and the printout apparently was discarded the report said 
a graduate student working at glendale school where the child is 
enrolled delivered the computer paper to the school to be used as 
scratch paper university officials said 
the committee finds no intentional connection between the use 
of the universitys computing system and the childs receipt of the 
paper on which the offensive material was printed the report said 
but it said the student who placed the file in the universitys 
system used another students access code and later demonstrated 
little remorse or concern 
the report recommended that guyon review procedures for obtaining 
access to university computers and decide whether the students 
involved should be disciplined 
the committee sincerely regrets that a child and his family 
were subjected to offensive materials that were reproduced on 
university facilities the report said 
</TEXT>
