<TEXT>
president bush on friday named rep richard 
cheney of wyoming as defense secretary moving with surprising speed 
to leave behind the controversy caused by john towers rejection by 
the senate 
bush said he would order the fbi to speed up its background 
checks to get the nomination moving too much time has been 
wasted here he said 
the president won a pledge of quick action from leaders of the 
senate armed services committee who praised cheney and said 
confirmation hearings would begin next week 
i know of no impediment to his nomination said sen sam 
nunn dga the armed services chairman who led the successful 
battle to kill towers nomination 
cheney 48 is a sixterm conservative congressman who served as 
white house chief of staff during the ford administration his 
selection was a surprise in view of his relative lack of experience 
on defense issues 
appearing with bush at a hurriedly called news conference cheney 
said he had an active interest in defense matters but 
acknowledged that obviously there are areas that i need to know 
and ill have to work hard on to master 
in naming cheney bush picked the no 2 man in the house gop 
leadership depleting his partys minority ranks there after a 
postcampaign pledge not to choose anyone from capitol hill for his 
cabinet 
this is the exception that proves that rule bush said when 
asked about his earlier declaration 
and cheney said i did agonize over leaving the hill where he 
has often said he enjoyed his work 
bush brushing aside the divisive battle over tower said 
thats history thats done however vice president dan quayle 
reignited the furor by accusing democrats of engaging in a 
mccarthyite mudslinging campaign against tower and waging an 
assault on the powers of the presidency 
commenting on quayles remarks bush said i cant tell you if 
he speaks for me i speak for myself he speaks for himself 
towers nomination was killed thursday on a near party line vote 
of 5347 in the democraticcontrolled senate he was defeated by 
concerns over his drinking habits his relationships with women and 
his work as a paid defense industry consultant after leaving 
government service 
bush praised cheney as a widely respected man of principle 
and predicted his nomination would go very fast and have 
smooth sailing 
democrats and republicans alike saluted the selection 
senate republican leader bob dole quickly hailed the appointment 
in a barbed comment that reflected the bitterness lingering from the 
tower confirmation struggle 
hes tough thats what we wanted a tough tough tough guy 
he said of cheney this time it will be a confirmation not an 
execution 
senate majority leader george mitchell of maine said cheney had 
served with distinction in congress he promised to work with 
nunn to ensure the nomination gets prompt consideration by the 
committee and the full senate 
sen tim wirth dcolo said hes a very able and impressive 
person hes one of the smartest people in congress 
an excellent choice said sen charles robb the freshman 
from virginia who was one of the last democrats to announce his 
opposition to tower 
in a joint statement nunn and sen john warner of virginia the 
ranking republican on the armed services committee said cheney is 
well known and highly respected by the members of the senate we 
have worked with him on many issues involving national defense and 
intelligence matters 
almost immediately after towers defeat the white house turned 
to cheney 
the congressman said he was contacted late thursday afternoon by 
white house chief of staff john sununu and national security adviser 
brent scowcroft then at 1 pm friday cheney went to the white 
house and discussed the job with bush 
i said i want to make a decision fast on this because i know 
him well and have known him well over the years the president 
said 
cheney said he checked with his cardiologist before accepting the 
job and was assured there were no medical restrictions to stop him 
a heart attack victim cheney underwent bypass surgery last august 
but returned to work three weeks later he said 
looking back at the handling of towers nomination bush said 
i may have made a mistake by holding it back pending fbi checks 
of allegations against tower there may have been some other 
tactical things that went wrong but please remember that when the 
nomination went up there it was very well received generally 
in response to reporters questions on star wars and a series of 
other defense issues cheney said i have extensive views on 
defense policy but i dont believe ill share them today 
bush was asked about his past declarations that tower was the 
best qualified candidate to head the pentagon 
i said that on december whatever it was and now were in march 
whatever it is and as of today dick cheney is the best and proper 
choice the president said in an appearance before reporters 
shortly after his departure for a weekend at camp david 
many potential candidates had been mentioned for the job 
including former rep jack edwards rala sens william cohen 
rmaine and ted stevens ralaska former defense secretaries donald 
rumsfeld and james schlesinger former cia deputy director bobby 
inman paul oneill chairman and chief executive officer of alcoa 
and norman augustine chairman and chief executive officer of martin 
marietta aerospace corp 
fitzwater at a latemorning briefing said bush reviewed 
candidates from any number of people and sources in the 
government in the white house and outside the government as well 
meanwhile quayle flew to indianapolis and in a speech harshly 
criticized senate democrats and warned there will be a lingering 
bitterness over the tower fight 
never in all my years in the senate have i encountered anything 
like the feeling of outrage that exists today among my former 
republican senate colleagues he said never have i encountered 
such anger and bitterness in the senate chamber 
