prominent lebanese international banker 
roger tamraz reappeared friday and denied reports he was kidnapped 
and held for ransom by a militia leader who lost money when his bank 
went under 
earlier friday however a tamraz business associate told the 
associated press in nicosia cyprus that the banker was freed after 
arranging to pay the final installment of a 3 million ransom 
tamraz 48 checked into the seaside west beirut summerland hotel 
shortly before sunset 
i was not kidnapped he said in an interview with the 
associated press i was on my own doing my own thinking 
tamraz who was reported kidnapped feb 19 said the ransom 
report was based on rumor and figment of the imagination and 
theres nothing to it 
the christiancontrolled radio station voice of lebanon said 
thursday that tamraz was being held by elie hobeika commander of a 
christian militia in the eastern bekaa valley town of zahle 
the report said that hobeika a former commander of the lebanese 
forces the main christian militia was forcing tamraz to pay 3 
million he claimed was owed him after the collapse of bank 
almashrek lebanons secondlargest bank 
tamraz who is a united states resident headed the christianrun 
bank until december when a run on its assets began an arrest 
warrant was issued for tamraz pending investigation of the banks 
affairs 
the respected newsletter middle east economic survey estimated 
almashreks deficit in lebanon at 100 million a largely 
stateowned conglomerate owned a major share in the bank 
tamraz fled from christian east beirut to the moslemheld western 
part of the capital in january and lived in the summerland hotel 
until shortly before his disappearance since last fall lebanon has 
had two rival governments one christian and one moslem 
the tamraz associate who spoke by telephone from paris and 
declined to be identified said a loan instrument was fixed to 
transfer the final 750000 in ransom money to the kidnappers 
through a swiss bank 
he said tamraz release was delayed for two days while the loan 
was arranged 
hobeika is held responsible for the september 1982 massacre of 
hundreds of palestinian civilians by christian militiamen in two 
beirut refugee camps after israel invaded lebanon the charge was 
confirmed by israeli reports but denied by hobeika 
in his interview friday tamraz predicted he would be vindicated 
of charges in connection with the banks demise investigators say 
the bank under his direction made shaky investments in spanish 
real estate and a moneylosing cargo airline it also took over 
three ailing banks and assumed their deficits 
in the past tamraz a maronite catholic blamed lebanese central 
bank governor edmond naim for deliberately undermining the bank in 
order to get rid of him 
