in 1940 unless rain falls more regularly than last year 
farmers are conservative and waiting for moisture he said 
thats the big factor my manufacturers are enthusiastic but im 
not 
thats because the farmers who survived the farm crisis are 
astute money managers who think long and hard before spending on 
average 60000 for a tractor and 110000 for a combine he said 
manufacturers like deere amp co of moline are upbeat about 1989 
prospects thats partly because deere enjoyed record earnings last 
year of 315 million despite the drought which produced the worst 
year of tractor and combine sales industrywide since records were 
