committee the ministry cannot yet realistically evaluate the damage 
which varies widely from region to region 
earlier the ministry released a preliminary estimate of 15 
billion but it said the amount of rain over the next few months 
could drastically alter the picture 
giuseppe avolio the president of the italian confederation of 
farmers said the damage could reach 74 billion 
so far the government has declared only sardinia a disaster area 
the island has had below average rainfalls for three years and 
