consuming countries are expected to call for the 
suspension of the current levy on traded cocoa at international 
cocoa organization talks opening here monday delegates said friday 
they are expected to argue a formal suspension is warranted 
because key cocoa producers have unilaterally stopped paying their 
share 
the levy of 30 a metric ton is collected by producers when they 
sell to cocoa organization consumers and by consumers when they buy 
from nonmembers 
the money is supposed to be forwarded to the cocoa organization 
headquartered in london to meet operational costs and to finance 
possible marketintervention measures 
the organization lacks the money to implement a proposed 
stockpiling scheme to stabilize prices in the current oversupplied 
market because of producer arrears totaling more than 80 million 
